      <h1 class='title'>Courts Agency</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 08 June 2004 vol 662 c4WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_4ws' title='Col. 4WS &mdash; HL Deb 08 June 2004 vol 662 c4WS' name='column_4ws' href='#column_4ws' rel='bookmark'>4WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0662P0-06995'>
        <a name='S5LV0662P0_20040608_LWS_3'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-charles-falconer' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0662P0_20040608_LWS_3' title='Link to this speech by Mr Charles Falconer' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-charles-falconer" title="Mr Charles Falconer">The Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs and Lord Chancellor (Lord Falconer of Thoroton)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0662P0-06995">The Queen has agreed that the new courts agency will be named Her Majesty's Courts Service when it is established in April 2005. The <a href="/acts/courts-act-2003">Courts Act 2003</a> allows the Lord Chancellor to create a new executive agency responsible for the administration of the magistrates' courts and the higher courts.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
